'''Yutani''' was a [[Human/Legends|Human]] [[Captain/Legends|captain]] in the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Alliance to Restore the Republic]] and a [[Scout/Legends|scout]] and a [[heavy weapon specialist]] in [[Alliance Special Forces/Legends|Alliance Special Forces]]. In the [[Standard year/Legends|year]] [[4 ABY/Legends|4 ABY]], Yutani attended a briefing held on the Alliance [[Flagship/Legends|flagship]] [[Home One/Legends|''Home One'']], during which Alliance [[Supreme Commander (Alliance)/Legends|Supreme Commander]] [[Mon Mothma/Legends|Mon Mothma]] discussed plans to [[Battle of Endor/Legends|attack]] the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire's]] [[Death Star II/Legends|second Death Star]] [[Battle station/Legends|battle station]].

==Biography==
Yutani, a [[Human/Legends|Human]], was a [[Captain/Legends|captain]] in the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Alliance to Restore the Republic]] during the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]]. Yutani served in [[Alliance Special Forces/Legends|Alliance Special Forces]] as a [[Scout/Legends|scout]] and a [[heavy weapon specialist]].<ref name="CCG" />

In the [[Standard year/Legends|year]] [[4 ABY/Legends|4 ABY]],<ref name="NEC">''[[The New Essential Chronology]]'' dates the events of [[Star Wars: Episode VI Return of the Jedi|''Star Wars'': Episode VI ''Return of the Jedi'']] to [[4 ABY/Legends|4 ABY]].</ref> Yutani sat at a briefing held on the Alliance [[Flagship/Legends|flagship]], the [[MC80A Home One Type Heavy Star Cruiser/Legends|Mon Calamari Star Cruiser]] [[Home One/Legends|''Home One'']], in which the Alliance's [[Supreme Commander (Alliance)/Legends|Supreme Commander]], [[Mon Mothma/Legends|Mon Mothma]], discussed plans to [[Battle of Endor/Legends|attack]] the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire's]] unfinished [[Death Star II/Legends|second Death Star]] [[Battle station/Legends|battle station]], which was [[Orbit/Legends|orbiting]] the [[Endor/Legends|moon of Endor]]. During the briefing, the Rebel leadership explained that members of a [[Endor strike team/Legends|strike team]] led by [[General/Legends|General]] [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]] would be sent to Endor to deactivate the [[SLD-26 planetary shield generator/Legends|SLD-26 planetary shield generator]] protecting the [[Death Star/Legends|Death Star]], thereby allowing Alliance [[Starfighter/Legends|starfighters]] to destroy the [[Space station/Legends|station's]] [[Hypermatter reactor/Legends|main reactor]].<ref name="ROTJ" />

==Personality and traits==
Yutani was a fair-skinned individual with [[Color/Legends|dark brown]] [[Hair/Legends|hair]] and a mustache.<ref name="ROTJ" />

==Equipment==
When in attendance at the briefing aboard ''Home One'', Captain Yutani wore the same [[uniform]] worn by other Rebel commandos at the briefing, and also wore a jacket that had an ammunition [[Bandolier/Legends|bandolier]] strung across.<ref name="ROTJ" /> Yutani carried custom [[repulsorlift compensator]]s to allow fluid movement with light [[Artillery/Legends|artillery]] weapons.<ref name="CCG" />

==Behind the scenes==
Yutani first appeared as a background character sitting at the Rebel briefing on ''Home One'' in [[1983]]'s [[Star Wars: Episode VI Return of the Jedi|''Star Wars'': Episode VI ''Return of the Jedi'']].<ref name="ROTJ" /> According to the fan website [http://www.aveleyman.com Aveleyman], Yutani was portrayed by an uncredited [[Gordon Hann]].<ref name="Aveleyman">{{WebCite|url=https://www.aveleyman.com/ActorCredit.aspx?ActorID=77299|text=Aveleyman - Gordon Hann|work=[http://www.aveleyman.com Aveleyman.com]|archivedate=20181105081438}}</ref> The character was later given a name and brief backstory on a card for the [[June]] [[1999]] ''[[Endor Limited]]'' expansion set of [[Decipher]]'s [[Star Wars Customizable Card Game|''Star Wars'' Customizable Card Game]].<ref name="CCG" />

